{
  "page": "Knights of the Vale",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:452px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/73/A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg/450px-A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/73/A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg/675px-A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/73/A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg/900px-A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A knight sworn to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a> - by Stephen Najarian</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>knights of the Vale</b> are the assembled forces of <a href=\"/index.php/Knights\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Knights\">knights</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quote\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quote</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The tradition of <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighthood</a> is strong in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale</a>. During the <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">coming of the Andals</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> first landed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Fingers\" title=\"Fingers\">Fingers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Legends claim that the first <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_Mountain_and_Vale\" title=\"King of Mountain and Vale\">King of Mountain and Vale</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Artys_I_Arryn\" title=\"Artys I Arryn\">Artys I Arryn</a>, was the <a href=\"/index.php/Winged_Knight\" title=\"Winged Knight\">Winged Knight</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale:_house_arryn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale:_house_arryn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The knights of the Vale are sent out in search of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_mountain_clans\" title=\"Vale mountain clans\">Vale mountain clans</a> on occasion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The lesser clansmen tend to be wiped out by these knights.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_events\">Recent events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hugh\">Hugh</a>, a young knight who squired in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> with the late <a href=\"/index.php/Defender_of_the_Vale\" title=\"Defender of the Vale\">Defender of the Vale</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Arryn\" title=\"Jon Arryn\">Jon Arryn</a>, is killed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand%27s_tourney\" title=\"Hand&#39;s tourney\">Hand's tourney</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Following her return to the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>, Jon's widow, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Lysa_Arryn\" title=\"Lysa Arryn\">Lysa Arryn</a>, forbids her knights from traveling to the capital to fight in the tourney.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> arrests <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> and takes him to her sister Lysa at the Eyrie. When Tyrion sarcastically replies to the accusation of murdering Jon, Lysa warns him to speak politely, for she is protected by the knights of the Vale. When Tyrion later demands <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a>, many knights and nobles ask for the honor of championing Lysa.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After winning his trial by combat against Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Vardis_Egen\" title=\"Vardis Egen\">Vardis Egen</a> thanks to his champion <a href=\"/index.php/Bronn\" title=\"Bronn\">Bronn</a> and departing the Eyrie, Tyrion appeals to the mountain clans, who reject his offers of <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>, by offering them weapons and armor to face the knights of the Vale.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Catelyn reunites with her son, <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>, she informs him that the only knight of the Vale that will join them is her uncle Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Tully\" title=\"Brynden Tully\">Brynden Tully</a>, formerly the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_the_Gate\" title=\"Knight of the Gate\">Knight of the Gate</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Despite their pleas for aid, Lysa ignores the messages urging the Vale to join forces with her nephew Robb, now the <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Trident\" title=\"King of the Trident\">King of the Trident</a>. After Robb ponders his next move after the betrayal of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rickard_Karstark\" title=\"Rickard Karstark\">Rickard Karstark</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, he considers that the knights of the Vale could make all the difference in the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> claims to <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> that the knights of the Vale will all pledge their swords to her to win her back <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">her birthright</a>, after she is wed to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harrold_Hardyng\" title=\"Harrold Hardyng\">Harrold Hardyng</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quote\">Quote</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quote\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>No men in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> are as bold and true as the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Lysa_Arryn\" title=\"Lysa Arryn\">Lysa Arryn</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>'s court</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>What do the <a href=\"/index.php/Stone_Crows\" title=\"Stone Crows\">Stone Crows</a> do, but hide behind rocks and shiver in fear as the knights of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale</a> ride by?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Shagga\" title=\"Shagga\">Shagga</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Knights_of_the_Vale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp;